## <a href="#call_nodes" name="call_nodes">CallNodes</a>

A CallNode is a ... OH GOD WHERE DO I START

If you want to _understand_ how it's all connected, [read the detailed Calls guide](/rest/calls/).

### <a href="#get_call_nodes_live" name="get_call_nodes_live">GET /call_nodes/live</a>

Get all current live nodes for the authorized user.

<%= response(
  call_nodes: [resource(:call_node)]
) %>

<h3><a href="#post_call_nodes_node_uuid_cancel_transfer" name="post_call_nodes_node_uuid_cancel_transfer">POST /call_nodes/:node_uuid/cancel_transfer</a></h3>

Cancel an active transfer. This is also what you want to do if you want to _take back the call_.

<%= parameters(
  node_uuid: "**Required.** UUID of the node."
) %>

**Returns status code `200`.**

<h3><a href="#post_call_nodes_node_uuid_node_uuid_hangup" name="post_call_nodes_node_uuid_node_uuid_hangup">POST /call_nodes/:node_uuid/node_uuid/hangup</a></h3>

Hang up the given CallNode.

<%= parameters(
  node_uuid: "**Required.** UUID of the node."
) %>

**Returns status code `200`.**

<h3><a href="#post_call_nodes_node_uuid_transfer" name="post_call_nodes_node_uuid_transfer">POST /call_nodes/:node_uuid/transfer</a></h3>

Start a transfer of the given call node to the given endpoint.

<%= parameters(
  node_uuid: "**Required.** UUID of the node.",
  endpoint: '**Required.** What to transfer to. Example: `Reception#1`.',
  type: '**Required.** Type of transfer.<br>Possible values: `[attended|direct]`.'
) %>

<h3><a href="#get_call_nodes_node_uuid" name="get_call_nodes/:node_uuid">GET /call_nodes/:node_uuid</a></h3>

Get info about a given CallNode.

<%= parameters(
  node_uuid: "**Required.** UUID of the node."
) %>

<%= response(
  call_node: resource(:call_node)
) %>

## <a href="#contacts" name="contacts">Contacts</a>

Contacts are additional info about a given phone number. They are either provided by Firmafon's internal lookups or by the employee or their colleagues ie. through an Integration.

### <a href="#get_contacts" name="get_contacts">GET /contacts</a>

<%= parameters(
  number: '**Required.** Example: `4512345678`'
) %>

<%= response(
  contact: resource(:contact)
) %>

### <a href="#post_contacts" name="post_contacts">POST /contacts</a>

Create a contact. These map to the fields `to_contact` and `from_contact` in Calls.

<%= parameters(
  'contact[number]' => '`4512345678`',
  'contact[name]' => 'Karsten Kontaktbegreb',
  'contact[email]' => 'karsten@example.com'
) %>

<%= response(
  contact: resource(:contact)
) %>

### <a href="#get_contacts_id" name="get_contacts_id">GET /contacts/:id</a>

<%= response(
  contact: resource(:contact)
) %>

### <a href="#put_contacts_id" name="put_contacts_id">PUT /contacts/:id</a>

Update a contact.

<%= parameters(
  'contact[number]' => '`4512345678`',
  'contact[name]' => 'Karsten Kontaktbegreb',
  'contact[email]' => 'karsten@example.com'
) %>

<%= response(
  contact: resource(:contact)
) %>

### <a href="#delete_contacts_id" name="delete_contacts_id">DELETE /contacts/:id</a>

<%= parameters(
  id: '**Required:** ID of the contact'
) %>

**Returns nothing with status code `200`**

## <a href="#employees" name="employees">Employees</a>

Employees are your colleagues.

### <a href="#get_employee" name="get_employee">GET /employee</a>

Returns an Employee object of the authenticated employee.

<%= response(
  employee: resource(:employee)
) %>

### <a href="#get_employees" name="get_employees">GET /employees</a>

Returns an array of the current employee's colleagues ordered by first name.

<%= response(
  employees: [resource(:employee)]
) %>

### <a href="#get_employees_id" name="get_employees_id">GET /employees/:id</a>

Returns a specific colleague.

<%= parameters(
  id: '**Required:** ID of the employee'
) %>

<%= response(
  employee: resource(:employee)
) %>

### <a href="#put_employees_id" name="put_employees_id">PUT /employees/:id</a>

Update an employee.

<%= parameters(
  id: '**Required:** ID of the employee',
  "employee[do_not_disturb]" => '`true` | `false`',
  "employee[dnd_timeout_at]" => '2013-12-16T17 =>12 =>26+01 =>00',
  "employee[employee_group_ids]" => "[1, 2] **Requires admin privileges.**"
) %>

<%= response(
  employee: resource(:employee)
) %>

### <a href="#post_employees_id_message" name="post_employees_id_message">POST /employees/:id/message</a>

Send an SMS to the given employee. **NB: These are cheap but [not free](https://www.firmafon.dk/prisliste/ "Firmafon Prisliste") - Look for "Web SMS".

The sender will be shown as either the current employee's number or name.

Not available for companies in trial.

<%= parameters(
  id: '**Required:** ID of the employee',
  "message[body]" => '**Required:** The contents of your message.'
) %>

<%= response(
  { sent: true }
) %>

